===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally [[𦔻]], hence {{Han compound|耳|口|t1=ear|t2=mouth(s)|ls=ic|nocap=y}} – to listen. Compare the top component of {{l-lite|zh|sc=Hani|聖}}.

Later, rewritten as {{Han compound|𡈼|耳|㥁|c1=p|c2=s|c3=s|t2=ear|ls=psc|nocap=y}} on the right.

The simplified version, [[𠯸]] (later stylized as [[听]]), is totally unrelated to the original character and it originally means "smiling".

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|s=听|alt=聴,聼,𦗟,𦔻-ancient,𠯸,𦔽,𦕢,𦕘,𦖆,𦘏,𪢧,咡}}
This is traditionally considered to have the same origin as {{och-l|聖|gloss=to hear; wise; sage}} and {{och-l|聲|gloss=sound}}. Additionally, it may be also related to {{och-l|聆|gloss=to hear; to listen}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}).

Outside connections unclear, although note {{cog-lite|qfa-lic-pro|*hliːŋ||to hear (it said)}} from Pre-Hlai ''*(h)leːŋ'' ({{zh-ref|Norquest, 2007}}).

Derivatives:
* {{och-l|廳|gloss=hall, i.e. where hearings take place}}
* {{och-l|廷|gloss=palace courtyard}}.

